{ 2. Develop your pieces as quickly and as actively as possible.

We do this for two reasons:

1. To give our pieces as much mobility (possible moves) as we can.
2. To clear the way for our other pieces to move.
3. To have our pieces working together as a team (like in football or any other team sport). }
 *


